| native name of the river if different from the English one, it is printed in brackets on the same line as '''name'''
|
|-
|'''other_name, other_name1 …'''
| other names of the river, it can be used for rivers with various names along their run
|
|-
! colspan="3" style="background: #cfcfcf" | Image
|-
|'''image'''
| a photograph of the river
|
|-
|'''image_size'''
| photograph size in pixels (set to 256 if left blank)
| 
|-
|'''image_caption'''
| photograph caption
|
|-
! colspan="3" style="background: #cfcfcf" | Etymology
|-
|'''etymology'''
| etymology (origin) of the river name, do not enter lengthy prose, examples:
* ''terre bonne'', French for good earth
* ''Penn'', [[William Penn]] and ''sylvania'', Latin for woods
* [[Thomas Jefferson]], when named for a person, add ''etymology_type = Named for''  
* [[Red River]], when named for a place, add ''etymology_type = Named for''
| '''_type (''Name origin''), _label, _note'''
